edu.sjsu.cs.cs151.controller.valve

Interface Valve

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Controller, EndMoveValve, EnterValve, LeftValve, LoadMapValve, RightValve, SpaceValve

    public interface Valve
    Valves performs certain actions based on their purpose. Each valve has three states: Executed, Missed, and Finished. If the valve has a different input than needed, it will throw a Missed flag Else, the valve will execute and finish accordingly.
    Author:
    Arman Sandher
